Walking through the product
Browsing and discovery
Anyone can search and filter listings by keyword and city with zero login required. Each result card carries an image carousel, category, tags, and price. It’s deliberately low-friction — the login wall only shows up when it needs to.
Trust, without oversharing
Open a listing and you get the full picture: description, category-specific attributes, a media gallery. But the seller’s contact details stay hidden until you log in and explicitly reveal them or open a chat request. It’s a small thing, but it’s the difference between a marketplace and a spam magnet
Press enter or click to view image in full size

Selling on Nova
Sellers get their own workspace: a dashboard of their live listings, and a create-listing flow that handles multi-image and video uploads, category-specific tags, and draft-to-review submission. How many listings a seller can post — and which features they can use — is governed by subscription plans with real entitlements (`listings.create=100`, `chat.messages=500`, and so on), not hardcoded limits

