Architecture
The part I’m most proud of architecturally: Nova isn’t just organized into feature folders — it’s organized into **portable modules**. Identity, listings, payments, chat, notifications, and other feature areas are each structured as self-contained packages with their own routes, providers, navigation, and permissions, with a manifest that describes them
import { novaIdentityModuleManifest } from '@nova/module-identity';
import { novaListingsModuleManifest } from '@nova/module-listings';registerNovaModules([
novaIdentityModuleManifest,
novaListingsModuleManifest
]);
using Nova.AuditLogs;
using Nova.Framework.DependencyInjection;
using Nova.Modules.Runtime;
using Nova.Tenancy;WebApplicationBuilder builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
_ = builder.Services.AddNovaFramework();
IReadOnlyList<ModuleDescriptor> modules = ModuleLoader.DiscoverFromApplicationBaseDirectory();
ModuleLoader.RegisterModules(builder.Services, builder.Configuration, modules);
WebApplication app = builder.Build();
app.UseNovaFramework();
app.UseNovaTenancy();
app.UseRateLimiter();
app.UseAuthentication();
app.UseNovaAuditLogs();
app.UseAuthorization();
app.UseNovaTenantModuleGate();
app.MapNovaModules(modules);
await app.RunAsync();
The rule each module follows: it can depend on shared platform package — never on another feature module directly, and never on the app shell. That constraint is what makes them portable.
In practice, it means the same identity, payments, and notification modules that run this marketplace could power a CRM or an internal HR tool just by swapping which manifests get registered. The marketplace is the first product built on top of it, not the only one it’s designed for.
Tech Stack

• Angular 20 standalone components, Signals, the new `@if` / `@for` control-flow syntax, `OnPush` everywhere

• Tailwind CSS extended with a custom token system (color, type, radius, shadow)

• RxJS for data orchestration — search-as-you-type, media carousels, chained API calls

• .NET API backend with real moderation, subscriptions, and payment analytics

• MSSQL server database

Let’s connect
If you’re building something similar, curious how any of this works, or just want to talk Angular architecture and design systems — I’d genuinely like to hear from you. I’m also open to freelance and contract work: full-stack developer.
Thanks for reading — and if you made it this far, drop a comment. I’d love to know what you’d build with a module system like this.
